<HEADLINE>
FT  26 SEP 94 / Arts (Openings): Chicago
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Even as rumours circulate that the Broadway version of 'Angels in America'
won't last out the year, Tony Kushner's Pulitzer, Olivier and Tony
Award-winning play enters another chapter as other productions open around
the US.
The national touring production of Angels' first half, 'Millenium
Approaches', opened last night at Chicago's Royal George Theatre, with the
second half, 'Perestroika' joining it in repertory from Thursday. Another
production of Millenium recently opened at Atlanta's Alliance Theatre; San
Francisco's American Conservatory Theatre opens its version of both halves
on October 12, while Houston's Alley Theatre launches its Angels next
spring.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>USZ  United States of America.
</CN>
