<HEADLINE>
FT  26 SEP 94 / Faulty drainage system causing puddles in tunnel
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHARLES BATCHELOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Eurotunnel, which operates Channel tunnel services, yesterday confirmed that
small amounts of water had collected in the tunnel because of a faulty
drainage system, Charles Batchelor writes.
The company, which is expected to launch passenger services next week,
denied that the accumulation was serious.
Eurotunnel said the tunnel had been designed to leak slightly and that five
pumping stations had been built to deal with the water. For every kilometre
of tunnel there were 600 joints in the lining of the wall. In four places
the drain designed to take away excess water had become clogged with silt.
The company said: 'We didn't expect the clogging but it is a very minor
issue. We are talking about a bucket or two of water over a matter of
weeks.' Only three of the pumping stations have had to be used.
</TEXT>
