FT  26 SEP 94 / Russia attracts investors
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN LLOYD
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MOSCOW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Russia is enjoying an upturn in foreign investment attracted by shares in
Russian companies, according to Mr Anatoly Chubais, Russia's deputy prime
minister for privatisation. He said share prices were soaring following the
end of the voucher auctions in June. The second phase of privatisation - the
selling of company stock for cash, with fewer privileges for the workers -
is now under way. Mr Chubais forecast that foreign investment would be
running at Dollars 1bn a month by the end of this year and would continue to
grow in 1995. It had totalled over Dollars 2bn in the first six months of
the year, and was growing by around 40 per cent a month. Brokers have also
reported a growth in portfolio investments in Russia this year.
