patterns and good make-for-price of the new Van Heusen range.
'I work with sleeves rolled up so double cuffs are not on. Jacket and tie
are not necessary in the office but for outside meetings a shirt must look
good under an unstructured, Italian suit. For work in the Far East, a white
shirt and jacket is the convention. I take cheap, short-sleeved ones but
they don't last long.'
